<br>
  The above having been said 3 things occurred that disturbed me personally and also a number of people that participated in the raid. I will try to state clearly and calmly what he issues were and want to make it clear this is not intended to be a whine session but rather a carefully thought out discussion of issues and hopefully some answers. I would also like to say that, even though there was loot involved in 2 of these issues the loot itself is not the issue at hand. I know azure has stated and I totally agree, Dragon raids are not about the loot. I personally go on dragon raids to have fun and to take down a big monster that is beyond the capability of doing so by myself or by my guild alone. I find it to be good raiding experience and practice for even bigger and better targets. This is not to say that the loot isn’t important or even desirable but so few items drop that to go on a dragon raid and to expect to get loot is just foolish IMHO. If I am lucky enough to win something or to get xp on a dragon raid, that is just icing on the cake.<br>
<br>
Here then are the issues that were witnessed by me or brought to my attention, some of it after the conclusion of the raid.<br>
<br>
#1<br>
During the lotto of items there was, on one of the items, an early roll. Not only that but the person rerolled at the correct time. KCoG lotto rules clearly state that if people roll early for an item then they are out on the lotto. This was repeated many times before and during the raid as well as being posted to this forum. This rule was not enforced. If there are rules and they are not enforced then they are not rules at all and will lead in the future others to expect the same bending of the rules to be applied to them. I would like to hear why this rule was not enforced and I would hope to also get an assurance that in the future, raid rules will be enforced. If the rules are not enforced it will just lead to chaos.<br>
<br>
#2<br>
<br>
The second issue involves the character Break. This person was not involved in the raid at any point until we were forming the buff line. They were not at the druid ring, they were not in the initial groups, and they were not part of the breaking process. Yet this person was allowed to roll on items. Again the rules clearly state if you do not show up on time then you will not be allowed to participate. Perhaps there is something I am not aware. Maybe this person had an alt at the raid from the beginning and then switched to the Break toon for the final assault on Naggy. Maybe they were personally invited, by Azure or another member of her raid leading team, to join the raid at that late time for some reason. In any case I would like to know, and if one of the above examples or some other good explanation is the reason that’s fine I just want to know, why this individual was allowed to join the raid so late and still roll on items. I have checked my logs so I know for a fact that Break was not present at the raid until just before we went through the buff line at least not as the toon Break.<br>
<br>
<br>
#3 <br>
<br>
During the raid while in the stone spider room (I think) an item dropped called a crystalline orb (? I think that’s what it is called). This is one of 2 items required for a high level SK pet spell. The other item needed is a prickly pear (? Again not certain on the name…. I’m no SK) and drops off the Icy terrors on the way to kill Vox. 2 vox raids ago one of these dropped and was lottoed off among all the present sks. This did not happen with the orb on the Naggy raid. The group that looted it kept it. It is my understanding, though I am not certain, that the group who looted this item and kept it didn’t even have an Sk in their group. So an item that is need only by an SK will end up in the hands of someone who didn’t even participate in the raid while those who did don’t even get a chance to roll on it. If I missed something please correct me but it seems to me that this of all the things that happened on the raid flies directly in the face of what KCoG is all about. KCoG was supposed to be a loose confederation of smaller guilds that, on their own, would not be able to go after big targets. This is something that comes from this type of raid and yet those KCoG members who were present were denied the opportunity to acquire something that they may only be able to obtain through an event like this. Of all the things that happened last night that appeared questionable, this is the worst one and I hope we can all get a clear explanation of why this occurred. If I had known this occurred at the time it would have been brought up before we left naggys lair but as it is I didn’t know at the time.<br>
<br>
#4<br>
<br>
Some of this next issue is second hand information so keep that in mind. After groups were formed we moved to the SS room. In the process, Gandorf, who was apparently trying to get there on their own instead of following directions, got lost and got themselves killed. The group leader was asked to go back to the zone entrance and help get gandorf back together. Somewhere along the line the group healer was there as well. It is my understanding (2nd hand remember) that Pslyth (group leader) and willowood (group healer) were told to wait at the zone line for instructions and they would be got back to the rest of the raid party. Gandorf, apparently, logged off shortly after dieing. These 2 members of the raid party were left sitting at the zone line. They were never brought up to the rest of the raid party. Did these people get forgotten? I find that hard to believe as one of them was supposed to be a group leader.<br>
<br>
<br>
Conclusion<br>
Sorry this got so long winded but I wanted to be thorough. I’d like to say that although issues 1 to 3 deal with loot the issue isn’t the loot it self but rather why rules are not being adhered to and in the case of #3 real issues of fairness are raised. Again its not about the loot its about why people are allowed to go outside the rules and no one seems to notice or care.  #1 seems to be the smallest issue. It seemed to me that azure a tsaryn (loot master) were trying to be lenient and not trying to be mean. While I can appreciate that and the lotto rules may seem harsh still the rules are there for a reason of if they are not adhered to then there will be no rules and no order. #’S 2 &amp; 4 are related to me as in one case you had folks show up and time and then, due to the acts of someone else, get left behind while someone who appeared to show up at the last possible minute was allowed to roll on loot that, by and large, they did not help to get to. #3 again to me is the most serious issue. Perhaps, as raid leader and loot leader you were not made aware that the orb dropped in which case this is not really a raid issue at all but rather an issue of who looted and then made off with an item that should have been lottoed. The only 2 people I know of that knew the orb dropped were Kcarcreve and Maed. Kcarcreve knew the orb had dropped and asked Maed if that was so. The reply was yes it had dropped and that was all that was said about it. Beyond that I do not know who else knew the orb dropped or why it was not lottoed but I would like an explanation. I’d like to think that there is a good and viable explanation as to why these things occurred and to have better communication during the raid so issues like this to not crop up again. My purpose here isn’t to be critical of the raid leadership but rather to get an explanation as to why these, at least to me, disturbing events occurred and ho to prevent them in the future.<br>
<br>
Patiently waiting a response and intelligent discussion,<br>
