<br>
If I'd had the same kind of completely un-ruly, obnoxious, un-disciplined pack of savages on the raids I was running... I don't think I would have done it as long as I did.  There's gonna be a lot of venom in the post, and I'm sad to say most of it is well deserved.<br>
<br>
First off, you NEVER, under ANY CIRCUMSTANCES, back-talk to or question the raid leader on an open channel.  If you have a problem with something they are doing, or think they have said something incorrect, let your group leader know, and let them pass it along.  If it's particularly urgent, send a tell.  Making comments in /ooc is out of line, and does not do anything at all to help the raid succeed.  If you are not going to be helpful, don't say anything.  It's pretty simple.<br>
<br>
Secondly... if you are spouting crap on an open channel, at least have the decency to have your information be correct.  I've been on a hell of a lot of Vox and Naggy runs, and a lot of what people were saying in objection to commands from Azure was just plain incorrect.  The amount of flak that came back from the order to camp out after pulling the lair spawns was appalling, and, as it happens, completely WRONG.  I've seen support people get kicked out of the zone by the dragon because they cast a buff on someone who still retained agro... someone who wasn't involved in the pull, only the fight in the room outside the lair.  Agro can transfer in really odd and un-predictable ways.  Camping is a safety measure, and a simple one at that.<br>
<br>
I mean come on...  camping and coming back... is that so hard?!  Good grief, on early KCoG raids, we'd camp out 5 or 6 times, and I rarely, if ever, heard anyone complain about it.  But some of you can't do it once without whining up a storm?<br>
<br>
And please, if you are a newbie on the raid, for your own good, shut the hell up.  The leaders and admin staff have been there, done that, and we know what we're doing.  If you think you know so much more, form your own damn alliance and try for yourself... don't come to a KCoG raid and make an ass out of yourself by giving someone as well traveled as Azure a hard time.<br>
<br>
And after all the crap that Azure and the admin had to put up with on that raid, I'm amazed things got handled as well as they did at the end.  You try sitting in a room full of screaming monkeys for 5 hours and see if your nerves aren't a little rattled afterwards.<br>
<br>
Yeah, maybe things could have been handled a little better in some cases, but frankly, I'm amazed Azure and Tsaryn handled them at all.  After a raid like that, I'd have just told everyone to come to West Commons the next day and we'd lotto off the drops then, because I'd have been too tired and pissed off to think clearly.<br>
<br>
All I can say is that if the kind of behavior, lack of discipline, and complete in-ability to listen to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>OR</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> follow directions is going to be common in the future of KCOG, I may just go and join an uber-guild, because there's no way I'd be able to put up with the kind of crap I saw tonight on a regular basis. <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
